snippet.textDisplay:
Can someone please explain the logic of updating the BIOS to enable the TPM settings instead of just... Ya know... Updating the TPM settings yourself? They both require the same amount of technical knowledge and the average computer user still won't even know what a BIOS update is so it's unlikely to help them at all anyway.

Furthermore, updating the BIOS comes with the risk of bricking the motherboard if power is cut so simply enabling the setting is far less risky for the average consumer.
